ht|r|at|Notice that in all of the above cases, opener's first bid was one of a suit and his rebid was 1NT, which describes a 
balanced 12-14 point hand. Responder's first bid was always one of a major.

Responder's second bid - 2@C or 2@D – aims to opener to give additional information about his holding in the majors.

Many play the convention after the following sequence:|
ht|v|cs|1|at|^m{|ia|1hp1sp1np!2c|at|}|
