ht|f|fp|1|cp|2|at|Another application of the Check Back Stayman convention can be used after opener's 2NT rebid.

In this context we should first refer to another question that appears frequently.

Look at the following hand:|
ht|k|cs|1|at|^c{|ih|psAJ42hK5dAK65cA94|at|}|
ht|l|cs|1|at|^l{|ia|1cp1hp?|at|}|
ht|r|fp|1|cp|2|at|The question is: should West show a balanced 18-19 point hand by jumping to 2NT or should he content 
with 1@S and show his strength later?

Though in my opinion 1@S will usually provide better results, many will give priority to 2NT.

Anyway, a partnership should have an agreement on whether or not an opener's rebid of 2NT denies 4-card spades.|
